HEADWORD: Simian
<hw>Sim"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>simia</ets>
an ape.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the family
<fam>Simiadae</fam>, which, in its widest sense, includes all the Old
World apes and monkeys; also, apelike.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>Any Old World monkey or ape.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

